{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"## Plan-refinement progress (2026-07-08, epic adept-hedge-stain continuation)\n\nRefined the plan across 4 plan-review rounds; grounded it in code-verified facts and surfaced the real design\ngaps. Capturing state so the continuation is clean. **B1 cannot fully close in one session** â€” the OPERATIONAL\ngates (â‰¥10 consecutive clean 20-min live shadow passes â‰ˆ 3+ hrs, + capped live heal, + flag flip) are wall-clock-\nbound. Deferring B1's completion; prioritizing the epic's closeable children (A3 closed; C2 in review; 9622/eca4\nCODE) first.\n\n### Code-verified facts (the plan now rests on these)\n- **The consumer swap is namespace-COMPATIBLE.** `_diff_fields` iterates `local_mapped` (JIRA names, e.g.\n  `\"summary\"`); `prev_snapshot[jira_key]` and `BindingStore.get_baseline` are BOTH JIRA-keyed (`_BASELINE_FIELDS`).\n  So feeding `get_baseline(local_id)` where `prev_jira_fields` is read is shape-for-shape compatible â€” no field-name\n  translation needed. `_INBOUND_MIRRORED_FIELDS` still holds the LOCAL `\"title\"`, a pre-existing partial no-op\n  (the guard never fires for summary/title) â€” UNCHANGED by the swap; document, don't silently fix.\n- **Corrupt-store is fail-closed at LOAD, not the consumer's job.** `get_baseline` returns None for BOTH absent and\n  non-dict (None = valid local-wins). A corrupt bindings.json raises in `BindingStore._load` at pass start\n  (binding_store.py:103-124). So the swap needs NO new corrupt-detection branch; None -> local-wins.\n- **No classifier-vs-legacy alert is buildable.** `classify()` runs only on OFF-snapshot pairs (binding_walk);\n  the field-differ owns ACTIVE bindings. No production path has both for the same binding -> a comparison needs a\n  parallel engine (forbidden). The EXISTING `baseline_shadow_check` IS the rollout divergence gate.\n- **`decision_census` is documented-but-never-emitted**; only `binding_walk_census` is live (run_differs.py:652).\n\n### Remaining plan gaps to resolve BEFORE claiming (all concrete now)\n1. **Flag propagation via `OutboundDiffConfig`** (outbound_differ.py:242-273 â€” the established config-dataclass\n   channel, has prev_snapshot/client/local_label_intent): add `baseline_consumer_swap: bool = False` there AND to\n   the dataclass in `src/rebar/_config_schema.py:355` AND the `_SECTIONS[\"reconciler\"]` coercer (~:464). Thread via\n   the config object, not ad-hoc kwargs. `local_id` is already in scope at `_compute_outbound_update_mutation`\n   (outbound_differ.py:622).\n2. **Streak persistence is a REAL code gap.** `SyncLogger.log` writes ONLY to the ephemeral\n   `bridge_state/sync-log-*.jsonl` (gitignored) â€” NOT stdout â€” so neither the sync-log NOR `gh run view --log`\n   yields the streak across runs. Options: (a) also print `baseline_shadow_check` to stdout in the pass\n   orchestration (tiny, makes GHA logs authoritative), or (b) commit a durable marker to the tickets branch. Pick\n   one and spec the empty/no-data fallback (treat as streak=0, not clean).\n3. **Live-heal RESTORE procedure** (not just backup+abort): explicit steps to restore from the Jira JSON export +\n   `git reset --hard pre-heal-<date>` on the tickets branch, with a rehearsal AC.\n\n### Consumer-swap seams (verified, for the implementer)\n- Two `_local_matches_prev` call-sites: outbound_fields.py:405 (direction-suppression) and :519-526 (conflict-sink).\n- `_diff_fields` already receives `binding_store`; thread `local_id` + flag; when ON compute\n  `baseline = binding_store.get_baseline(local_id)` once and substitute for `prev_jira_fields`."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783564151834493001,"uuid":"47611e45-270b-4bb3-867b-c184aa6e6076"}